if anybody wants to go check it out.

00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:14.000
Yeah, I think potentially we have a lot of people

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:16.000
that are using GitHub Actions in creative ways.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.000
But I think for those of you

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.000
who are not yet using GitHub for version control,

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:22.000
whether you work in teams or by yourself,

00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:24.000
like, it does open up a lot of flexibility

00:22:24.000 --> 00:22:26.000
for you to be able to accelerate

00:22:26.000 --> 00:22:29.000
and do a lot less, like, duct tape work.

00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:32.000
Like, I think for two of those projects I mentioned earlier,

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:34.000
like, for months I would wake up at 7 a.m.

00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:36.000
and I'd literally log in and I'd run some scripts

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:38.000
and then it would be magically updated

00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:40.000
until I finally got to the point where it was continuously,

00:22:40.000 --> 00:22:42.000
you know, being able to be deployed.

00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:45.000
So Connect Cloud specifically,

00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:47.000
and as the example you saw with the DigitalOcean,

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:49.000
like, if you go out to a GitHub repo,

00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:51.000
like, there are a lot of things already

00:22:51.000 --> 00:22:53.000
sort of baked into those environments

00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:56.000
that allow you just to say, well, if I push my code here

00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:58.000
and maybe it passed certain tests,

00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:00.000
it will automatically push to Connect Cloud.

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:03.000
And I never even really need to log into Connect Cloud

00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:05.000
until I have other things that I need to be doing.

00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:07.000
Yes, that's what I do.

00:23:07.000 --> 00:23:09.000
I'm like, I have this app, it's up there,

00:23:09.000 --> 00:23:12.000
and then I just push the change,

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:15.000
or, you know, I'll push to a branch and then I'll do a PR

00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:17.000
and that PR will have to pass tests

00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:18.000
or I'll have to review it.

00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:20.000
And then once that goes to main,

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:22.000
my app is just updated immediately.

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:24.000
And it happens so fast.

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:26.000
Like, I can just sit there and watch it

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:28.000
from one second to the next.

00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:31.000
As soon as I push it, it's updated and it's amazing.

00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:33.000
There was one other thing I wanted to call out,

00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:34.000
which is Nick Drew said,

00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:36.000
another question for this slide that would be good

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:38.000
