00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:48.000
especially when you're using GitHub, right?

00:30:48.000 --> 00:30:50.000
So you can have your initial deployment

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:51.000
for something you're confident in.

00:30:51.000 --> 00:30:55.000
That is a single deployment tied to that custom name

00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:57.000
and then have that point to your main branch.

00:30:57.000 --> 00:30:59.000
But if you're working like on a development branch,

00:30:59.000 --> 00:31:02.000
you could do another deployment from that dev branch

00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:04.000
and then share that out and like, you know, get feedback.

00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:05.000
Like, is this ready to go?

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:06.000
Are we good?

00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:07.000
You can test it yourself.

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:09.000
And then as soon as that is ready,

00:31:09.000 --> 00:31:12.000
you can either either change your initial deployment

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:15.000
just to use, you would just push that to main

00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:17.000
